        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "For over a decade you were the lead singer of DEMON TORPOR, the biggest sludge metal band on the West Coast.  You were often compared to Kyuss, but you guys were much bigger by album sales and you'd only pressed two full albums.  Sure the band had been on hiatus for a few years and Zim the drummer overdosed, but you were getting it all back together before this whole vampire thing.  You knew shouldn't have let that groupie in to your place, but you just couldn't help yourself and that was the end of your life. The cops packed you off to the morgue and the press was all over it.  You're just lucky you didn't burn in the sun in the process.  Thankfully a couple of Brujah showed up just before you ate the medical examiner and they got you out of there.  They called themselves Anarchs and they thought you'd be safer with some other secret society of Vampires called the Camarilla, so they handed you off to the Brujah in the valley. Now you've got figure out how you're going to piece everything back together. To make matters worse, you're sick. Vampires aren't supposed to get sick, and you don't manifest symptoms. But every time you try and make a ghoul, an empowered mortal servant, by feeing someone your blood, they get sick and they usually don't make it. One of your Anarch contacts said this sometimes happens, but he didn't know a way to cure it."
        ],
